    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-29T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-29T04:30:00-05:00" n="256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–2050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Richards</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-29T13:00:00+03:30"
                            >June 29, 1950—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1242. Dept inform Army, Navy, Air. Initial reaction President Truman’s statement
                    re Korea<note n="1" xml:id="d256fn1">For the text of the President’s statement,
                        issued on June 27, see <ref target="frus1950v07#pg_202">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>, p. 202</ref>.</note> is one of mixed
                    approbation and concern. No press comment to date due to complete absorption
                    local press with Razmara appointment.<note n="2" xml:id="d256fn2">Razmara had
                        been appointed Prime Minister on June 26.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Most officials with whom we have spoken feel US support of Korea has called
                    Soviet bluff. Minority feels Soviets not bluffing and that Iran is next on
                    Soviet list.</p>
                <p>Department pass Moscow. Sent Department 1242, repeated info Moscow 125.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richards</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
